\b 2.2.5. System Interfaces\par
\b0
The current build is defined mainly by internal runtime interfaces rather than external service integrations.\par

Table 2.5. Implemented system interfaces\par
Interface | Purpose | Implemented through\par
Menu and profile interface | Create or continue local progress | MainMenuScript, PlayerProgressProfileStore\par
Scenario selection interface | Choose level and scenario | LevelSelectSceneController, LevelScenarioCatalog\par
Call Phase interface | Gather and report incident information | Transcript UI, IncidentReportController, AssessRisk flow\par
Cross-scene flow interface | Transfer pending scene and mission data | LoadingFlowState\par
On-site gameplay interface | Execute mission actions and interactions | FPSInteractionSystem, FPSInventorySystem, IncidentMissionSystem\par
Bot command interface | Command AI teammates | FPSCommandSystem, BotCommandAgent\par
Review interface | Display mission result and completion data | MissionEndOverlayController and related UI\par

\b 2.2.6. Constraints and Assumptions\par
\b0
The concept of operations of the current build is shaped by several practical constraints and assumptions.\par

Table 2.6. Constraints and assumptions\par
Type | ID | Statement\par
Constraint | C-01 | The product is scoped as a single-player desktop game\par
Constraint | C-02 | The software operates offline and uses local persistence only\par
Constraint | C-03 | Scenario quantity and mission complexity are limited by capstone scope\par
Constraint | C-04 | Runtime behavior depends on local Unity scene wiring and asset configuration\par
Constraint | C-05 | Some repository content remains experimental or work in progress\par
Assumption | A-01 | Players have basic keyboard-and-mouse literacy\par
Assumption | A-02 | The game supports training and instruction, not formal certification\par
Assumption | A-03 | Mission evaluation is based on software-defined objectives and score logic\par
Assumption | A-04 | Scenario execution depends on local configuration, not external live systems\par
Assumption | A-05 | The simulation abstracts reality in favor of repeatable learning flow\par

